-- Russia’s Sugar Output Reaches 4.9 Million Tons, Union Says
-- B y   M a r i n a   S y s o y e v a
-- 2012-01-17T13:12:16Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-17/russia-s-sugar-output-reaches-4-9-million-tons-union-says.html
Russia ’s sugar output from
domestically-produced beets rose about 81 percent to 4.9 million
metric tons from the start of the marketing year on Aug. 1
through Jan. 11, compared with a year earlier, the country’s
Sugar Producers’ Union said.  A total of 41 facilities refined 38.4 million tons of beets
to produce the sweetener, the union said today on its  website .
Output from beets was 2.7 million tons a year earlier, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
